d item size to compute the priority score.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = bins - item\n    return np.where(available >= 0, available / (bins + 1e-8), 0) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + 1e-8)\n```\n\n### Function 9:\nThis implementation uses the available space and the bin size to compute the priority score.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = bins - item\n    return np.where(available >= 0, available / (bins + 1e-8), 0) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + 1e-8) * np.std(bins)\n```\n\n### Function 10:\nThis implementation calculates the available space and uses it with the bin size and item size to compute the priority score.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = bins - item\n    return np.where(available >= 0, available / (bins + 1e-8), 0) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + 1e-8) * np.std(bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins))